{{Infobox person | name = Roopak Saluja | image= Roopak Saluja 2016.jpg | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1975|7|25}} | birth_place = [[New Delhi]], [[India]] | occupation = Founder & Chief Executive Officer - The 120 Media Collective & Sooperfly, Media entrepreneur | education = Doon School & INSEAD | spouse = {{marriage|[[Tara Sharma]]|November 2007}} }} '''Roopak Saluja''' (born 25 July 1975) is an Indian media businessman and [[angel investor]]. He is the founder and [[chief executive officer]] of The 120 Media Collective - a communications & content group comprising subsidiaries, Jack in the Box Worldwide, Sniper and Bang Bang Films; and Sooperfly - A new media company that is building content brands direct-to-audiences. He has been featured in Campaign India's A-List of the Most Influential People in India's Advertising, Media & Marketing Industry 2010, 2011, 2012 and 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.campaignasia.com/page/40under40_saluja|date=January 2016}}</ref>
==Early life== Saluja was born on 25 July 1975, to a Punjabi father and a [[Nepal]]ese mother. He did his schooling at the [[Doon School]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dsobs.net/RB-Jan-2013/46_RB-Jan-2015.php|title=DSOBS|last=Makhijani|first=Design: R. Makhijani / Author: R.|website=www.dsobs.net|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref> in [[Dehradun]] and studied at [[INSEAD]] in [[France]] and [[Singapore]].
==Career== He started his [[advertising]] career at 23, in account management at [[Young & Rubicam]] [[Budapest]]. After that he moved to [[Ogilvy & Mather]] [[Paris]] to work for [[Motorola]] Europe, Middle East and Africa. He quit Ogilvy in 2003 to go to business school at [[INSEAD]].
===Bang Bang Films=== In mid-2006, after graduating with an [[MBA]] from INSEAD, he set up a company called Bang Bang Films.<ref>{{cite web|author=CB |url=http://www.campaignbrief.com/asia/2010/11/bang-bang-films-and-believe-me.html |title=Bang Bang Films and Believe Media tie up |publisher=Campaign Brief Asia |date=2013-03-18 |accessdate=2013-07-02}}</ref> Bang Bang Films was ranked #2 on AllWorld Network's Top 25 fastest growing companies, across all [[sector (economic)|sector]]s, in [[India]] in 2010.{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}
In July 2013, Bang Bang Films and [[Film director|director]] [[Jim Sonzero]] created a joint venture primarily focused on beauty, lifestyle and storytelling. It first project was a [[L’Oreal]] Fall Repair campaign with [[Bollywood]] [[actor]] [[Sonam Kapoor]], and the company shot another spot for L’Oreal starring [[Aishwarya Rai]].{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}
Bang Bang Films was ranked among the Top 5 Production Houses in India by [[advertising agency]] professionals in [[The Economic Times]] supplement, Brand Equity's Agency Reckoner 2014 list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/42630018.cms|title=BE Agency Reckoner 2014: Nirvana of 'Incredible India' fame is best film production agency - The Economic Times|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/brand-equity/be-agency-reckoner-2014-nirvana-of-incredible-india-fame-is-best-film-production-agency/articleshow/42630018.cms|title=BE Agency Reckoner 2014: Nirvana of 'Incredible India' fame is best film production agency - The Economic Times|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref>
===Jack in the Box Worldwide=== Jack in the Box Worldwide was set up in 2009 as the content-for-brands arm of Bang Bang Films. It combines content strategy, [[film]], [[video production]] and [[digital media]] to create customized content for brands across multiple platforms and geographies. It has offices in Mumbai and Delhi.<ref>{{cite news|last=Samosa |first=Social |url=http://www.socialsamosa.com/2013/08/jack-in-the-box-worldwide-opens-office-in-new-delhi-appoints-new-business-heads/ |title=Jack in the Box Worldwide Opens Office in New Delhi. Appoints Business Heads for Mumbai and Delhi |publisher=Socialsamosa.com |date=2013-08-14 |accessdate=2014-03-21}}</ref>
Roopak is a member of the Indian Angel Network, a group of entrepreneurs who invest in start-up businesses across a variety of sectors and [[market (economics)|market]]s. In 2011, ''[[CNNGo]]'' listed him among 20 people to watch out for in [[Mumbai]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Jhunjhunwala |first=Udita |url=http://www.cnngo.com/mumbai/life/people-who-matter-2011-769045 |title=20 people who matter in Mumbai in 2011 |publisher=CNN Travel |date=2011-01-26 |accessdate=2013-07-02}}</ref>
In 2014, Roopak was featured on Campaign Asia-Pacific's "40 Under 40" list among the region's strategic thinkers, suits, creators and planners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.campaignasia.com/page/40under40.aspx|title=Campaign Asia-Pacific's 40 under 40 (2014) {{!}} Campaign Asia|website=www.campaignasia.com|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.campaignasia.com/page/40under40_saluja.aspx|title=40 under 40: Roopak Saluja {{!}} Campaign Asia|website=www.campaignasia.com|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref>
==Personal life== He is a professional [[trance music|trance]] [[DJ]], and has performed in Europe, South Africa and Thailand, and co-founding and running his own trance label, Procyon Records (Budapest and Paris).{{citation needed|date=January 2016}} He has also acted in ''[[Marigold (2007 film)|Marigold]]''.{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}
He married [[actress]] [[Tara Sharma]] in November 2007.<ref name="intoday1">{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Star+struck/1/20054.html |title=Star struck: Simply Mumbai |publisher=India Today |date=2008-11-14 |accessdate=2013-07-02}}</ref> They have two children together, sons born in 2009 and 2011.
